         "id": "SECTION_introduction",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### Introduction\n\nJust as we did in the first level of the game (<htcite0>), our goal here is to reinforce our knowledge of numerical representation, but this time we will do it with numbers of more than one digit.\n\nAlthough the way we represent numbers on two of the abacuses — Soroban and Suanpan (算盤) — (<htcite1>; <htcite2>; <htcite3>) is not exactly the same as that used in the Inca Yupana or even in the Mesoamerican system (<htcite4>; <htcite5>), the logic of the numerical sequence is the same in any of these systems.\n\nThus, in this second level, we will first use the abacuses of China (Zhongguo 中國) and Japan (Nippon koku o Nihon koku, 日本国), and then the numerical systems of *Abya Yala* (América).",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "1e8e2b4c-03ed-4b98-b9e2-f678b5b36a84",
